title: Grateful Dead Live at Dane County Coliseum on 1978-02-03
lineage: Dat (Sony PCM-R500) > Tascam DA-3000 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC
description:
Set I
Cold Rain & Snow, Mexicali Blues-> Big River, They Love Each Other, Looks Like Rain, Loser, Passenger, Brown Eyed Women, El Paso, Peggy-O, The Music Never Stopped
Set II
Good Lovin', Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Playin' In The Band-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: Great recording This is like two nights before, only better. After a slew of mostly unimpressive shows throughout January, the Dead pull out all the stops. In particular the 2nd set suite is a masterpiece.

got to see a little furthur.. Oh My oh My, I had already given the Second Set Only Soundboard 5 stars
and now I get to hear the entire show in Soundboard.
Just realizing that the better the sound quality 
the more I enjoy the show
and the more I enjoy the show
the better I am feeling..
This First set is great
lots of jams
High intensity Keith
Great Vocals
The set really builds
I am just at B.E. Women
and they are picking up momentum 
Thinking on how Looks Like Rain
Had filled out since they broke it out
heading off to Europe (3-21-72)
and I got to say
Viva La Difference
Thanks Donna Jean!
and thanks Bobby.
Great spot for El Paso
they are already revved up 
Bob losing the lyrics
but the band is on
Peggy O is just a slight step back
a cool drink of water.
While MUSIC is one of those Summer tunes
It has a warm the heart feel
3rd of February in Wisconsin.
Good surging jam around 4 minutes in
which they ride layer and even meltdown.

OMG! MP3 Say it ain't so...
6 first set songs were sourced from MP3!?!?!?!
How could you!?

I saw that and had to make a "comment," useless though it is... Knowing our pristine sensibilities, and the purity of our community... almost sounds like... nevermind!
Oh to have some SBD MP3s of 6/24/70!

Listening on the day 44 years later... I wasn't around to witness Jerry and the gang perform, so I sometimes like to listen to shows with the same date as that day (in this case, Feb. 3rd). Some can be stinkers, most of the time they're great, but now and then, I'll happen on one that's just fucking awesome. This is one of those shows; it starts with bombastic energy in Cold Rain and Snow that doesn't really diminish throughout both sets. Super thankful that there's a soundboard recording of this. Love it!
